events.name: New York Knicks at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Cameron Payne scored 21 points, Devin Booker added 20 and the Phoenix Suns used a dominating second half to beat the New York Knicks 116-95.
headlines.shortLinkText: Payne, Booker lead Suns to 116-95 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma had 28 points, 10 rebounds and five assists and the Washington Wizards, after watching star Bradley Beal limp off in the last minute, beat the Charlotte Hornets 106-102 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma scores 28 points, Wizards beat Hornets; Beal limps off

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had 33 points and seven assists and the Sacramento Kings extended their winning streak to six games with a 137-129 win over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings beat Pistons 137-129, extend winning streak to 6 games

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving was playing again. Ben Simmons was playing like an All-Star again.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving returns, Simmons scores 22 as Nets beat Grizzlies

headlines.description: — The smiles, jokes and laughter returned to Cleveland's locker room following Sunday night's win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland scores 25, Osman 20 as Cavaliers blast Heat 113-87

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson scored a season-high 41 points and Steph Curry added 33 as the Golden State Warriors beat the Houston Rockets 127-120 on Sunday night for their first road win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson nets 10 3s, has 41 points in Warriors' 1st road win

headlines.description: — Denver coach Michael Malone was looking for any kind of help on a two-game swing through Dallas with two-time MVP Nikola Jokic and two other starters missing.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rare buzzer-beater helps outmanned Nuggets beat Mavs 98-97

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 30 points and 18 rebounds, and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the San Antonio Spurs 123-92 Sunday night to win three straight games for the first time since the first week of January.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis leads Lakers past Spurs for 3rd straight win
